   {:e #blake3 "d870d9968ef1726984a2b161c5e4564e9b817e13400c238f612787b67fe890c2" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :task/t-4e98cf9a; META-FAILURE: We have had this EXACT conversation before — 'check the spec before designing.' The fact that it recurs means the methodology is not self-enforcing. The reconciliation step decays under k* pressure EVERY TIME. Process obligations don't work. The fix must be STRUCTURAL: braid spec create and braid task create should REQUIRE reconciliation evidence before accepting the transaction. Not a hint. Not a warning. A GATE. Just like CBV (Completion Before Verification) gates task closure on acceptance criteria, CRB (Creation Requires Background) should gate spec/task creation on reconciliation with existing knowledge. If spec_relevance_scan returns 3+ matches, the create command should REFUSE unless --reconciled flag is passed (attesting the agent reviewed related elements). This is the same pattern as CBV but for the CREATION side, not the COMPLETION side.; Creation Requires Background — CRB Gate; Session entity: :task/t-520c155c; THE EPISTEMOLOGICAL PRINCIPLE: All new knowledge must be RECONCILED with existing knowledge before it becomes actionable. The observe→crystallize→task→execute cycle is INCOMPLETE. The correct cycle is: observe → RECONCILE → crystallize → task → execute. Reconcile = query the store for everything related to the new observation, identify overlaps/contradictions/extensions, and only THEN crystallize. Without reconciliation, new knowledge may duplicate or contradict existing knowledge — which is EXACTLY what happened with the evidence lattice (5th parallel confidence system). This is the DEEPEST failure mode: not missing knowledge, but having knowledge that isn't activated at the moment of decision. The store HAD ADR-STORE-008, INV-WITNESS-002, ADR-UNCERTAINTY-001, ADR-RESOLUTION-012. None were surfaced until an explicit Explore agent was sent. The system should make reconciliation AUTOMATIC,